00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:05,480
will be properly entranced
by the sight of a Beaurevel
on a spirited Arab?

435
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:08,960
A preliminary rendezvous
has been arranged.

436
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:15,400
I'm not interested in details.
In that case, perhaps
I should drop the whole matter.

437
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:17,560
Is that what you want? No.

438
00:44:17,560 --> 00:44:23,680
Then there are certain
other expenses to be met.
I found a delightful old boathouse

439
00:44:23,680 --> 00:44:25,600
on the Bayou St Jean.

440
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:34,160
You may have even used it yourself.
It will take a certain amount of
money to make it properly enticing.

441
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:41,680
You already have 25,000 dollars.
I won't touch that. I'm treating it
as a sentimental trust. Paul...

442
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:46,040
perhaps we HAD better drop...
AUNT EULAH: Barbara! >

443
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:48,080
Wish me well, Cousin.

444
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:22,680
I was afraid you wouldn't come.
I was afraid YOU wouldn't. My dear
lady, there's far too much at stake.

445
00:45:22,680 --> 00:45:27,240
The most beautiful women
in New Orleans were at our party,
you outshone them all.

446
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:36,280
What's the matter? That was
my first party and my last. Good,
then I'll have you all to myself!

447
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:40,920
I don't think you understand.
I'm not going to see you any more.

448
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:43,160
You've heard gossip about me.

449
00:45:43,160 --> 00:45:50,280
Whatever you've heard happened
long before I met you. It has
nothing to do with you. What gossip?

450
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:56,720
Never mind. What are you trying
to say? Meeting you at the ball
was so important to me.

451
00:45:56,720 --> 00:46:01,240
I know it's not your problem,
it's mine. And mine alone...

452
00:46:02,240 --> 00:46:04,920
And I'm not unaware of your charm.

453
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:06,960
The Beaurevel luck.

454
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:09,480
You also know I'm a married woman.

455
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:15,000
The Beaurevel luck! Exactly, you're
a Beaurevel with money, position...

456
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:19,120
I dare not see you again.

457
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:21,640
Have you considered MY feelings?

458
00:46:21,640 --> 00:46:25,160
I want to stop it
before there are any feelings.

459
00:46:25,160 --> 00:46:27,600
I see. Oh, how charming!

460
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:34,840
Corinne, you're right,
we won't see one another again.

461
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:36,360
Oh, no!

462
00:46:37,480 --> 00:46:42,160
Well, what I mean is,
maybe we shouldn't be too hasty.

463
00:46:43,920 --> 00:46:48,440
Maybe it won't be as difficult
as I thought. No, it won't be
difficult at all.

464
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:59,960
Every year, our budget becomes
larger. Because every year there
are more students, more teachers.

465
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:06,400
I suppose progress is costly.
By the way, how's Lucas making out?
Fine  a good man.

466
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:11,040
I'm delighted to hear that. I was
a little worried. About what?

467
00:47:11,040 --> 00:47:17,640
It's nothing of any consequence.
Lucas's background is perhaps
not the most desirable,

468
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:19,720
but it's of no consequence.

469
00:47:19,720 --> 00:47:27,280
What about Dr Lucas's background?
It's ridiculously inadequate for the
importance of the position he holds.

470
00:47:27,280 --> 00:47:34,320
He worked as a common labourer
on the docks one time. Yes, so he
could study medicine at night.

471
00:47:34,320 --> 00:47:38,840
I'm glad to see you so vigorously
defend one of your faculty,

472
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:45,280
however Lucas's contract
is up soon and you might want
to find someone more suitable.

473
00:47:45,280 --> 00:47:52,960
But Dr Lucas has a brilliant future.
Some day you'll be proud we had him
on our Faculty. I hope you're right.

474
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:09,320
I hope I'm not disturbing you.
Close the door quietly, please,

475
00:48:09,320 --> 00:48:12,560
I don't want any little gusts
of air.

476
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:17,880
You made me miss!

477
00:48:17,880 --> 00:48:20,320
I'm extremely sorry. Not at all.

478
00:48:20,320 --> 00:48:22,480
A mathematical experiment?

479
00:48:22,480 --> 00:48:24,520
No, it's a gambling game.

480
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:28,640
I paid my way through college
with it. Sit down, please.

481
00:48:28,640 --> 00:48:34,680
But that's your chair.
It's my only chair but you're
trustee of the university.

482
00:48:34,680 --> 00:48:38,560
I happen to have a friend...
You're a lucky man.

483
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:40,600
This friend has noticed

484
00:48:40,600 --> 00:48:48,000
that Miss Beaurevel seems to take
rather a dangerous interest in you,
if I may be blunt. Oh, do be blunt.

485
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:50,320
Well, there you are.

486
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,080
Where?

487
00:48:52,080 --> 00:48:56,280
A Creole would understand.
I come from upstate New York.

488
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:58,960
Coffee, Mr Duchaine? No, thank you.

489
00:48:58,960 --> 00:49:06,080
I'm in a position to secure for you
a full professorship at any
of several Northern universities.

490
00:49:06,080 --> 00:49:09,640
May we be blunt again, Mr Duchaine?
By all means.

491
00:49:09,640 --> 00:49:14,920
You're bribing me to relieve Miss
Beaurevel of my dangerous presence.

492
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:21,400
I'd much rather you didn't put it
that way. I know. We Northerners
are so crass.

493
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:25,440
So how much would you pay me
in addition to the job?

494
00:49:25,440 --> 00:49:27,880
You leave me at a loss, Lucas.

495
00:49:27,880 --> 00:49:31,920
I come from a very old
and honourable family in New York

496
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:35,960
and my honour is necessarily
expensive. Would, er...

497
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:40,640
5,000 dollars be too much
for your mythical friend?

498
00:49:40,640 --> 00:49:43,240
5,000 dollars is a lot of money.

499
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:49,120
Let's be business-like, Mr Duchaine.
5,000, yes or no? Very well.

500
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:56,400
I'll arrange for you to leave this
university at once. Do they still
have duels in New Orleans? Why?

501
00:49:56,400 --> 00:50:04,200
When you realise what a fool you've
been, you may want to challenge me.
You've been laughing at me.

502
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:09,200
Forgive me, there's so little
to laugh at around here, unless you
want to join me in a game of chance.

503
00:50:10,960 --> 00:50:14,120
Gently with the door, please,
it deflects the cards.

504
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:32,160
Hello, Cousin. Get out of my room!
Happily, as soon as you've given
me a cheque for 25,000 dollars.

505
00:50:32,160 --> 00:50:35,720
I gave it to you. You promised me
a similar amount

506
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:39,920
when a certain transaction
was concluded. And you have?

507
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:44,480
The esteemed Dr Lucas will not be
dining at home this evening.

508
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:49,760
He will be working in his laboratory
through the night. How elevating!

509
00:50:49,760 --> 00:50:56,160
Don't be charming, Paul.
I can't help it. Even when
you slapped me, I was charming.

510
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:59,200
What do women see in you?
You nauseate me!

511
00:50:59,200 --> 00:51:06,800
Corinne will meet me at 9:30 and
may I say that she would have come
sooner if she could have got away.

512
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:09,400
All right, Paul. And the cheque?

513
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:11,720
Tomorrow.

514
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:14,640
Amazing, isn't it? I trust you.

515
00:51:14,640 --> 00:51:18,480
We're both nauseating people,
aren't we, Cousin?

516
00:51:38,560 --> 00:51:40,720
I must get a lock for that door.

517
00:51:40,720 --> 00:51:43,160
That's the wrong door to lock.

518
00:51:43,160 --> 00:51:48,160
Look, I'm busy. Say whatever you
came to say and then leave me alone.

519
00:51:48,160 --> 00:51:52,280
This probably won't interest you
but... Probably not.

520
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:56,920
I remember your telling me
how cheap I was... Yeah, I remember.

521
00:51:56,920 --> 00:52:00,360
That's why you ought to lock
your door at home.

522
00:52:00,360 --> 00:52:04,360
I think you'd better be
very careful of what you say next.

523
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:07,680
I will be
only the exact truth.

524
00:52:07,680 --> 00:52:14,520
While you're here saving humanity,
your wife is out with another man,
being human.

525
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:20,760
Your stories are
like anonymous letters. People
pay very little attention to them.

526
00:52:20,760 --> 00:52:26,520
Do you remember a certain boathouse
on the bayou? Vaguely. That's where.

527
00:52:26,520 --> 00:52:28,560
Now may I get back to work?

528
00:52:28,560 --> 00:52:30,600
Of course you may...

529
00:52:30,600 --> 00:52:32,640
if you can!

530
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:38,480
Hell hath no fury...

531
00:53:00,280 --> 00:53:03,680
MARK'S WORDS ECHO
'Happiness doesn't grow like that.

532
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:10,320
'There's no use trying to explain
anything to you like an adult
so let's forget it.'

533
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:14,960
MR TOPLADY: 'I'm not sure I like
the feeling behind your smile.

534
00:53:14,960 --> 00:53:18,400
'I trust you'll use the money
wisely.'

535
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:22,160
PAUL: 'We're both nauseating people,
aren't we?'

536
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:53,640
May I have some more wine?

537
00:53:54,640 --> 00:53:56,080
Do you need some more?

538
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:03,640
Paul, don't. Why not? You came
to meet me in a deserted boathouse.

539
00:54:07,920 --> 00:54:09,440
No!

540
00:54:09,440 --> 00:54:16,920
I don't like cheap affairs.
Neither do I. Darling, you're
just what I've always looked for.

541
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:22,360
I'd want to marry you even if you
weren't a Beaurevel and were poor.

542
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:28,680
That's sweet but I never discuss
marriage with married women.
I could get a divorce. For me?

543
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:36,440
Yes, darling. I'm constitutionally
opposed to marriage. I don't see
why that should spoil our evening.

544
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:41,560
But I do. No, you don't. No! I told
you I don't like cheap affairs.

545
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:47,440
I see how Lucas got caught.
He was the first step up the ladder
for you. Paul!

546
00:54:47,440 --> 00:54:49,000
I don't intend...

547
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:57,560
I'm sorry, Corinne.
I didn't mean to...

548
00:54:57,560 --> 00:54:59,080
Corinne.

549
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,400
Corinne!

550
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:48,360
Mark.

551
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:58,920
Go on home.

552
00:56:00,280 --> 00:56:02,800
Go on home and stay out of this!

553
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:11,800
< DOOR CLOSES

554
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:23,000
Hello, Barbara. I suppose
you're annoyed with me.

555
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:29,720
I had a change of heart
and failed to keep the appointment
at the boathouse. I was there, Paul.

556
00:56:30,960 --> 00:56:32,680
I saw you run away.

557
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:38,960
It was an accident. You killed her.
I told you it was an accident!

558
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:45,720
I had no intention of even
hurting her. Mark found the body.
Did he see me? What did he say?

559
00:56:45,720 --> 00:56:47,760
He told me to go home.

560
00:56:47,760 --> 00:56:49,800
To stay out of it.

561
00:56:51,800 --> 00:56:53,320
Yes...

562
00:56:53,320 --> 00:56:55,360
Very proper.

563
00:56:55,360 --> 00:56:57,800
He'll protect your fair name.

564
00:56:57,800 --> 00:57:04,840
Association with the better
families of New Orleans has taught
him the manners of a gentleman.

565
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:08,240
They'll think he did it.
Yes, they will.

566
00:57:08,240 --> 00:57:10,680
In any event, he'll find himself

567
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:15,040
in a rather unpleasant situation.
What are you going to do?

568
00:57:15,040 --> 00:57:16,440
Me?!

569
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:22,840
Remember that you're
equally involved, and perhaps
in a more distasteful fashion.

570
00:57:22,840 --> 00:57:24,920
Are you going to the police?

571
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:28,480
Why, of course not!
If I'd admitted to this affair

572
00:57:28,480 --> 00:57:32,760
there wouldn't be a decent house
in New Orleans open to us.

573
00:57:32,760 --> 00:57:36,160
And I don't think
you're going to the police.

574
00:57:36,160 --> 00:57:41,400
You don't want the newspapers
to know about your unholy ancestry!

575
00:57:41,400 --> 00:57:45,800
They'd realise that you come
by your depravity quite honestly!

576
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:55,920
We spent the evening at home. You
were playing the piano  I heard
you. And I was reading  you saw me.

577
00:57:59,560 --> 00:58:01,600
A very good book, too!

578
00:58:05,640 --> 00:58:09,080
Barbara dear, no-one is worth
so much worry.

579
00:58:09,080 --> 00:58:14,160
Look at our acquaintances and our
friends  revolting, aren't they?

580
00:58:14,160 --> 00:58:18,680
This research fellow
isn't even one of our circle.

581
00:58:18,680 --> 00:58:21,280
Barbara, forget them, all of them.

582
00:58:21,280 --> 00:58:23,360
Let's consider ourselves.

583
00:58:23,360 --> 00:58:27,560
You once said we were
nauseating people. You were right.

584
00:58:27,560 --> 00:58:29,680
Of course!

585
00:58:29,680 --> 00:58:31,720
Good night, Cousin.

586
00:58:40,240 --> 00:58:44,800
But if Lucas did it, why did
he call the police? Don't be naive.

587
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:51,120
He wanted to avoid suspicion.
He killed his wife...
I refuse to believe he's guilty.

588
00:58:51,120 --> 00:58:56,760
Even you must believe that this
has somewhat vitiated his merit.

589
00:58:56,760 --> 00:59:00,040
I rescind Dr Lucas's contract.

590
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:07,480
See that he leaves at once. Surely
you realise the injustice of this?
My fellow trustees agree with me.

591
00:59:07,480 --> 00:59:08,840
Gentlemen?

592
00:59:08,840 --> 00:59:11,080
Good day, Dean. Good day, sir.

593
00:59:11,080 --> 00:59:13,120
I'm sorry, Dean.

594
00:59:13,120 --> 00:59:15,160
Good day, sir.

595
00:59:18,720 --> 00:59:20,760
KNOCK AT DOOR

596
00:59:20,760 --> 00:59:22,800
Come in.

597
00:59:25,840 --> 00:59:27,880
Come right in.

598
00:59:33,080 --> 00:59:35,920
Wouldn't you like one
of my little pets as a keepsake?

599
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:37,960
The inquest is tomorrow.

600
00:59:39,040 --> 00:59:41,080
I know.

601
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:45,440
I've been setting MY house in order,
how about yours?

602
00:59:45,440 --> 00:59:50,400
It was an accident, but
it's my fault  Paul's  not yours.

603
00:59:50,400 --> 00:59:52,920
I've read enough Sherlock Holmes

604
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:59,600
to be able to figure that out
by myself(!) All right, I've ruined
your life and your career,

605
00:59:59,600 --> 01:00:02,840
tell me what to do.
What else is there to do?

606
01:00:02,840 --> 01:00:07,120
You've made a clean breast of it,
your conscience is clear.

607
01:00:07,120 --> 01:00:13,640
Mark! Isn't that really
why you came to me? Do you
really not know what to do?

608
01:00:13,640 --> 01:00:18,280
Isn't there an absolute refusal
on your part to face yourself?

609
01:00:18,280 --> 01:00:24,240
You never will,
that's why our back-door affair
was held in such strict privacy.

610
01:00:24,240 --> 01:00:26,280
From the beginning

611
01:00:26,280 --> 01:00:32,880
you were afraid of what
your charming aristocracy might
think of it. Maybe you're right.

612
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:37,320
Now you'll have all the time
in the world to think about it.

613
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:41,920
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'd like to say goodbye
to the rest of my little friends.

614
01:01:04,240 --> 01:01:06,680
CORONER: Have the doors closed.

615
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:10,880
MAN: The inquest is in session.
The doors will be closed.

616
01:01:10,880 --> 01:01:14,920
This is an inquisition
into the death of Corinne Lucas.

617
01:01:14,920 --> 01:01:21,440
It is the responsibility
of the jurors to judge
from the evidence introduced

618
01:01:21,440 --> 01:01:26,000
whether the death was from
natural causes, from an accident,

619
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:28,440
or as the result of homicide.

620
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:34,960
It is not the jurors' duty
to judge any of the witnesses
either guilty or not guilty,

621
01:01:34,960 --> 01:01:37,680
but it is within the jurors' duties

622
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:44,560
to advise me to deliver the body
of any person whom they think
is responsible for such homicide.

623
01:01:44,560 --> 01:01:47,000
Call the first witness, please.

624
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:53,240
Who else was in the boathouse
when you got there?
This gentleman here. Dr Lucas.

625
01:01:53,240 --> 01:01:55,760
What was the attitude of Dr Lucas?

626
01:01:57,000 --> 01:02:00,520
I can't seem to think
there was any attitude.

627
01:02:00,520 --> 01:02:03,200
Was the room in any disorder?

628
01:02:05,480 --> 01:02:07,720
Well, yes, sir.

629
01:02:07,720 --> 01:02:14,240
Did it appear that there may have
been a struggle? I was certain.
Thank you, Sergeant.

630
01:02:14,240 --> 01:02:16,280
Next witness, please.

631
01:02:16,280 --> 01:02:21,840
Doctor, the deceased was found
partly in the fireplace.

632
01:02:21,840 --> 01:02:26,160
Would a fall against an andiron have
caused her death? I should say so.

633
01:02:26,160 --> 01:02:32,120
Was the fall a natural one?
Even an attack of vertigo
would not cause such a fall.

634
01:02:34,120 --> 01:02:40,000
I don't know why in the world
you came here, Barbara.
Why did you, Barbara?

635
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:44,560
Barbara's interested in
these sordid spectacles and so am I.

636
01:02:44,560 --> 01:02:48,680
Thank you, Doctor, that is all.
Next witness, please.

637
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:55,880
Where did you go when you left the
university? To the old boathouse
on the lake. And what did you find?

638
01:02:55,880 --> 01:02:57,920
My wife was dead.

639
01:02:57,920 --> 01:03:02,160
You say she died before you arrived.
That's what I say.

640
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:09,480
What made you go to the
old boathouse? You had important
research scheduled for that night.

641
01:03:09,480 --> 01:03:13,000
I had a premonition.
What kind of premonition?

642
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:16,520
I'm afraid it's beyond explanation.

643
01:03:16,520 --> 01:03:20,920
Just a premonition?
No-one gave you information?

644
01:03:20,920 --> 01:03:27,720
No-one. What did you expect
to find when you reached
the boathouse? I don't know.

645
01:03:27,720 --> 01:03:35,160
You had no idea that your wife might
be there with another man? Look,
this is an inquest, not a trial.

646
01:03:35,160 --> 01:03:41,800
You're supposed to find out facts,
not motives. You wouldn't
understand my motives.

647
01:03:41,800 --> 01:03:45,240
Back to your arrival
at the boathouse

648
01:03:45,240 --> 01:03:49,440
you say it was empty except
for the body of your wife. Yes.

649
01:03:49,440 --> 01:03:53,800
So there is no witness
for or against you? If there were,

650
01:03:53,800 --> 01:03:58,120
do you think he or she
would refuse to come forward?

651
01:03:59,120 --> 01:04:02,560
Careful, Barbara,
it's showing in your face.

652
01:04:02,560 --> 01:04:07,400
Dr Lucas, your manner is so evasive
and your facts so uncertain,

653
01:04:07,400 --> 01:04:11,440
that I feel that you are
withholding the truth from us!

654
01:04:11,440 --> 01:04:18,120
May I remind you that you are
in a situation of great jeopardy.
I don't need to be reminded.

655
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:22,840
Then you have nothing further
to tell this investigating body?

656
01:04:22,840 --> 01:04:24,880
Nothing further.

657
01:04:24,880 --> 01:04:32,240
Even though you will be taken
into custody for indictment before
a grand jury? Nothing further.

658
01:04:32,240 --> 01:04:39,280
Wait! Have you any evidence?
Mr Coroner... Yes, Mr Beaurevel.
My cousin is overwrought.

659
01:04:39,280 --> 01:04:46,320
May she be excused? The jurors will
disregard this outburst. The good
name of the Beaurevels will...

660
01:04:46,320 --> 01:04:48,360
The good name?

661
01:04:48,360 --> 01:04:52,720
Carrie Crandall's name?
I'm the granddaughter
of the notorious Carrie Crandall!

662
01:04:56,000 --> 01:05:02,520
Let this witness stick
to pertinent facts. Dr Lucas's wife
was dead before he got there.

663
01:05:02,520 --> 01:05:08,960
My cousin Paul was with her.
I bribed him to meet her
with Carrie Crandall's money.

664
01:05:08,960 --> 01:05:12,760
I tried to stop it but I failed.
I was there outside when she fell,

665
01:05:12,760 --> 01:05:17,040
and I saw him run away
before Dr Lucas got there. These
are the facts and I swear to them.

666
01:05:21,960 --> 01:05:26,520
This inquest is recessed
until ten o'clock tomorrow morning.

667
01:05:26,520 --> 01:05:30,400
Spectators, please leave.
The jurors are dismissed.

668
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:32,440
Blood will tell,

669
01:05:32,440 --> 01:05:34,960
my angelic cousin.

670
01:05:34,960 --> 01:05:37,560
You're coming with me, Beaurevel.

671
01:05:37,560 --> 01:05:41,240
Not MR Beaurevel?
You're coming along with me!

672
01:05:49,120 --> 01:05:52,160
Barbara... Oh, Aunt Eulah!

673
01:05:52,160 --> 01:05:58,600
If only I could have spared
you this. I warned you
not to take that money.

674
01:05:58,600 --> 01:06:04,640
I hope all your days
will be as empty and bitter
as you have made mine.

675
01:06:04,640 --> 01:06:09,880
Stay away from me and stay away
from my house. You and
your grandmother are two of a kind!

676
01:06:11,440 --> 01:06:13,840
Oh, Mark, take me away!

677
01:06:13,840 --> 01:06:17,200
Anywhere,
wherever it is I can hide.

678
01:06:17,200 --> 01:06:19,240
You can't hide,

679
01:06:19,240 --> 01:06:21,400
and you can't leave here yet.

680
01:06:21,400 --> 01:06:24,000
I can't bear to face anybody again.

681
01:06:24,000 --> 01:06:26,040
Please!

682
01:06:26,040 --> 01:06:29,520
There are a few things
that you'll have to face.

683
01:06:29,520 --> 01:06:34,160
You'll be at the inquest
when it reopens. You'll have
to face the people.

684
01:06:34,160 --> 01:06:36,840
You'll have to face yourself
finally.

685
01:06:39,080 --> 01:06:41,280
You know it just could be...

686
01:06:41,280 --> 01:06:43,720
that if you do all those things,

687
01:06:43,720 --> 01:06:47,160
you might turn out to be
quite a woman.

